CCDI utilizes both Precipitation and GRACE-TWSA data. It can identify the drought caused due to either deficit in Precipitation or TWS or due to partial contribution of both. For CCDI computation, we first found the Precipitation Anomaly (PA), the deviation of monthly precipitation from their mean monthly precipitation. Deviation of monthly PA from their mean monthly PA, we get Precipitation Anomaly Residual (PAR). Similarly, we have to find the Terrestrial Water Storage Anomaly Residual (TWSAR) by taking the deviation of monthly TWSA from their mean monthly TWSA. After computation of TWSAR and PAR, we have to find Combined Deviation (CD), the summation of TWSAR and PAR. By standardization of CD, we get CCDI.2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
